Class Lion

  • java.lang.Object
    • Animal
      • Lion
  • public class Lion
extends Animal
    A simple model of a lion. Lions age, move, eat rabbits (if they're female) and foxes (if they're male), fight (male vs male) and die.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    David J. Barnes, Michael KÃ¶lling and Daniel Lowry

    • Constructor Detail

      • Lion

        public Lion​(boolean randomAge,
            Field field,
            Location location,
            int ba,
            double bp,
            int mls,
            int rfv,
            int ffv)
        Create a new lion at location in field. A lion can be created as a new born (age zero and not hungry) or with a random age and food level.
        Parameters:
        randomAge - If true, the lion will have random age and hunger level.
        field - The field currently occupied.
        location - The location within the field.
        ba - Breeding age passed from settings tab.
        bp - Breeding probability passed from settings tab.
        mls - Max litter size passed from settings tab.
        rfv - Rabbit food value passed from settings tab.
        ffv - Fox food value passed from settings tab.

    • Method Detail

      • act

        public void act​(java.util.List<Animal> newLions)
        This is what the lion does most of the time: it hunts for foxes and rabbits. In the process, it might breed, fight other male lions, die of hunger, or die of old age.
        Specified by:
        act in class Animal
        Parameters:
        newLions - A list to return newly born lions.

        private Location findFood()
        Look for rabbits adjacent to the current location. Only the first live fox or rabbit is eaten.
        Returns:
        Where food was found, or null if it wasn't.

      • giveBirth

        private void giveBirth​(java.util.List<Animal> newLions)
        Check whether or not this fox is to give birth at this step. New births will be made into free adjacent locations.
        Parameters:
        newLions - A list to return newly born lions.

      • breed

        # Generate a number representing the number of births, if it can breed.

      • canBreed

      • fight

        Check whether there is an adjacent male lion. If so kill it.
